STANDARD: Folkhälsomyndigheten (Swedish Public Health Authority) provides specific temperature guidance. General minimum: 18°C operative temperature. For "känsliga personer" (sensitive persons): 20°C minimum. For "särskilda boenden för äldre" (special housing for elderly): 22-24°C recommended. This is a concrete regulatory reference with population-specific temperature bands.

Furillen äldreboende (Gotland): Sweden''s first pandemic-adapted care home, explicitly incorporating "demensvänlig miljö" (dementia-friendly environment) with Thermotech climate systems.

Tarkett/University of Stirling DSDC: Swedish-distributed design guide specifically for dementia care environments. Floor and wall design rated by DSDC for dementia suitability.

ADVERSARIAL: NCT07189507 clinical trial specifically testing whether 26°C upper indoor temperature limit is suitable for older adults — directly challenging standard comfort models. Finding: "this may necessitate a lowering of recommended upper indoor temperature limit during hot weather" for elderly populations.

CROSS-JURISDICTIONAL SYNTHESIS:
- SV is ONLY jurisdiction found with population-stratified temperature guidance (general vs sensitive vs elderly care).
- PMV-PPD not validated for elderly.
- "Symptomless cooling" documented in EN literature.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10 22:24','session_2026-05-10f-term-alias-expansion');
