CTE DB-SUA requires LRV >30 points for door-wall contrast (aligns with UK/AU LRV tradition). ≥50% luminance contrast for elevator buttons (UNE-EN 81-70). Mixed approach: uses LRV for some elements, percentage for others.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:40:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('luminance-contrast-lrv-evidence-base','ZH','SEARCHED',2,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

GB 55019-2021 §2.11.4 requires only qualitative ''color or material difference'' from adjacent pavement. No numerical contrast threshold. GB 50763-2012 similar. Medium yellow recommended. Even more qualitative than JP approach.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:40:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('luminance-contrast-lrv-evidence-base','IT','SEARCHED',2,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

DM 236/89 requires ''good luminance contrast (light-dark), minimum 40%'' between architectural elements. Regional codes (e.g. Veneto DGR) add ''contrasto cromatico'' for stair nosings. Percentage-based, similar to FR approach.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:40:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('luminance-contrast-lrv-evidence-base','KO','SEARCHED',1,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

Korean accessibility law and guidelines require yellow tactile blocks as standard; allow ''clearly contrasting'' alternatives when yellow unsuitable. No numerical luminance contrast threshold specified. KS F 4561 covers block specifications. Qualitative approach like JP and CN.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:40:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
