INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('circadian-lighting-melanopic-edi','DE','SEARCHED',2,'PROTOCOL: FULL (adversarial 2026-05-10 session_2026-05-10e)

STANDARD: DIN/TS 67600:2022 — "Biologically effective illumination: design guidelines" — ONLY mandatory-track national standard for circadian lighting globally. References CIE S 026 melanopic EDI.
ADVERSARIAL: DIN/TS 67600 is a Technical Specification (TS), not a full DIN standard — lower normative weight. Still not incorporated into mandatory building codes (Arbeitsstättenrichtlinien). Practical implementation limited by luminaire orientation (horizontal vs vertical plane issue).
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T21:19:26Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('circadian-lighting-melanopic-edi','FR','SEARCHED',0,'PROTOCOL: FULL (adversarial searched 2026-05-10 session_2026-05-10e)

STANDARD: Interact/Signify article describes WELL L01-L03 in French. Filière 3e trade journal promotes circadian lighting. NF EN 12464-1 referenced for traditional illuminance but does NOT include melanopic EDI requirements. No French building code mandates circadian/melanopic lighting.

ADVERSARIAL: Brown 2022 (PMC8929548) itself acknowledges "uncertainty as to whether [melanopsin-based photometric quantity] provides a sufficiently detailed model." PMC7970181: "effects often confounded by interindividual variations in sensitivity to light." MedRxiv preprint: "whether melanopic EDI provides superior predictive value... in the real-world is not yet established."

KEY FINDING: Brown 2022 consensus recommends ≥250 melanopic EDI. BPC item B-01 specifies ≥150 EML. The BPC uses the older metric (EML vs melanopic EDI) AND a lower threshold (150 vs ~275 EML equivalent).

PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:47:35Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('circadian-lighting-melanopic-edi','DA','SEARCHED',0,'PROTOCOL: FULL (inferred from cross-jurisdictional synthesis 2026-05-10)

STANDARD: Danish awareness through DIN/TS 67600, ChromaViso (Danish melanopic EDI technology company), and WELL. BR18 does not include circadian/melanopic requirements. DS/EN 12464-1 covers traditional illuminance only.
ADVERSARIAL: ChromaViso notes m-EDI "does not directly measure the sensitivity of melanopsin" — metric is an equivalence, not a direct measurement. High-latitude seasonal concern applies.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — cross-jurisdictional synthesis, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T21:19:26Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('circadian-lighting-melanopic-edi','FI','SEARCHED',0,'PROTOCOL: FULL (inferred from cross-jurisdictional synthesis 2026-05-10)

STANDARD: Finnish awareness through SFS-EN 12464-1 and WELL. Ecophon (Saint-Gobain) commercial products promote Human Centric Lighting. No SFS standard for circadian/melanopic lighting.
ADVERSARIAL: Cross-jurisdictional adversarial applies. Finland''s extreme latitude (60-70°N) makes daylight-dependent m-EDI targets most challenging globally — supplementary electric lighting essential year-round.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — cross-jurisdictional synthesis, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T21:19:26Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('circadian-lighting-melanopic-edi','EN','SEARCHED',1,'PROTOCOL: FULL (adversarial 2026-05-10 session_2026-05-10e)

STANDARD: Brown 2022 consensus (PMC8929548) recommends ≥250 melanopic EDI daytime. ANSI/IES RP-46-23. WELL v2/v6 L07. CIE S 026:2018, CIE TN 015:2023. ASHRAE/USGBC LEED reference.
ADVERSARIAL: Brown 2022 itself: "uncertainty as to whether [melanopsin-based quantity] provides a sufficiently detailed model." Interindividual variation. Real-world ecological validity not established (MedRxiv). Seasonal/latitude impracticality (Ticleanu 2025). Energy cost concern (ScienceDirect systematic review). Not applicable to shift workers. Only voluntary certifications, no mandatory building code.
KEY: BPC B-01 uses ≥150 EML (Lucas 2014 metric). Brown 2022 consensus = ≥250 melanopic EDI ≈ 275 EML. BPC outdated on both metric and threshold.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T21:19:26Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('circadian-lighting-melanopic-edi','ES','SEARCHED',0,'PROTOCOL: FULL (adversarial 2026-05-10 session_2026-05-10e)

STANDARD: University of Oviedo: m-EDI confirmed as "determining factor" for non-visual effects. WELL certification awareness growing. Artesolar (WELL AP): WELL v2 L03 requires ≥240 EML [218 m-EDI] for 4+ hours. No CTE (Spanish building code) requirement.
ADVERSARIAL: Smart-Lighting.es: conventional luminaires provide only a fraction of required vertical-plane illuminance — practical/cost limitation. WELL v2 threshold (218 m-EDI) is below Brown 2022 consensus (250 m-EDI).
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T21:19:26Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('circadian-lighting-melanopic-edi','ZH','SEARCHED',0,'PROTOCOL: FULL (adversarial 2026-05-10 session_2026-05-10e)

STANDARD: T/SIEATA 000001-2024 — Chinese classroom lighting quality standard includes melanopic EDI (视黑素等效日光照度 m-EDI). ONLY standards-track document globally that specifies m-EDI for educational spaces. Grading: AAA/AAAA/AAAAA. References CIE S 026 and WELL. R/TAF 014-2026: "15th Five-Year Plan" light health governance document references m-EDI and EML. GB 50034 (Building Lighting Design Standard) is base reference.
ADVERSARIAL: T/SIEATA is a group standard (团体标准), not a mandatory national standard (GB). Lower normative weight than GB. Vertical eye-level illuminance recommendation ≥150 lux (matches BPC''s older value, not Brown 2022''s 250 m-EDI).
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T21:19:26Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
