INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','DE','SEARCHED',2,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION

Snoezelen well-established in care/school/therapy settings. No DIN standard for sensory room design (DIN 4102 B1 for fire safety of materials only). Individual-needs-based approach. Adversarial: ideological objections from normalization/integration advocates against dedicated sensory rooms.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','FR','SEARCHED',3,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Snoezelen well-established in FR care settings. HAS includes Snoezelen in Bonnes Pratiques Professionnelles. Three distinct concepts: (1) coin calme (low-tech classroom retreat), (2) salle sensorielle (broader MSE), (3) espace Snoezelen (trained-practitioner-led, specific methodology). User autonomy mentioned ("promotion de l''autonomie", "sentiment de contrôle") but within PRACTITIONER-MEDIATED framework — accompagnateur "contrôle et adapte la stimulation" based on user reactions. This is NOT equivalent to BPC''s user-control-as-primary — it''s mediator-controlled with user-responsive adaptation.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) Cairn.info review: 41.7% of studies reported unfavorable cost-effectiveness; Snoezelen is a registered trademark (marque déposée) creating commercial bias in evidence base. (2) CLE Autistes (autistic-led FR org): non-consensual hypostimulation rooms = "grave maltraitance" — consent is essential ethical boundary. (3) No NF standard for sensory room design.
SEARCH QUERIES: "salle sensorielle Snoezelen autisme contrôle utilisateur recherche étude" + "salle sensorielle Snoezelen critique limites efficacité preuve autisme"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: FR practice partially supports BPC prior (user autonomy valued) but implementation is practitioner-mediated, not user-controlled. Genuine nuance, not full divergence like ZH.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','DA','SEARCHED',4,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Sanserum established in Danish care/education. Sensory Design I/S subcontracts to Center for Autism DK. Autismeplatform emphasizes individual assessment. MultiCare.dk: "Snozelen er en ikke-direktiv terapiform, som altid bør tage udgangspunkt i borger fremfor terapeut" (non-directive, always user-centered). Hundreds of sanserum in Denmark.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) VISS Skanderborg: McKee et al. 2007 found NO evidence for Snoezelen in autism — behavior may WORSEN. (2) Lotan & Gold 2009 meta-analysis: NO significant effect for intellectual disabilities. (3) MultiCare.dk acknowledges "snoezelen har fået ryg for, at være en støvsamler" (reputation as dust collector in some institutions). (4) VISS questions whether positive effects come from Snoezelen itself or from staff being more attentive. (5) Documentation/evidence is described as a major challenge: "hvordan dokumenterer man oplevelser og en forbedret livskvalitet?" (how to document experiences and quality of life?).
SEARCH QUERIES: "sanserom autisme design bruker kontroll Norge Danmark" + "sanserom Snoezelen kritikk begrensning evidens autisme Norge Danmark"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: CONTESTED. Danish knowledge center explicitly questions Snoezelen efficacy for autism. User-centered principle stated but evidence base is challenged. McKee 2007 adversarial finding is the strongest counter-evidence found in any language so far — directly from the autism population.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','FI','SEARCHED',3,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Aistihuone in Finnish disability services and Autismisäätiö day activities. Nurmi 2019 thesis: aistihuone for autistic children, Snoezelen method — emphasizes "yksilölliset tarpeet ja mieltymykset" (individual needs and preferences) and user must have "tarpeeksi aikaa tehdä itse valinnat" (enough time to make own choices). Autismisäätiö Kotka: nature-based aistihuone where clients PARTICIPATED in design and construction — genuine participatory design example. Käypä hoito (Finnish clinical guidelines): practical environmental modifications focus on LOW-STIMULUS strategies (dimming, muted colors, minimalism, sound-absorbing textiles) as PRIMARY approach, with aistihuone as supplementary.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) No Finnish-specific adversarial study on Snoezelen/aistihuone efficacy found. (2) Scandinavian adversarial applies: SPEDUCULT/Lund 2020 (no certified education across Nordics), McKee 2007 (no evidence for autism), Lotan & Gold 2009 (no significant effect for ID). (3) Käypä hoito framing is consistent with NL finding: low-stimulus environment is PRIMARY design strategy; aistihuone is SUPPLEMENTARY. (4) Finnish theses are applied/practice-based (AMK/UAS level), not controlled research — evidence quality is practitioner-descriptive, not experimental.
SEARCH QUERIES: "aistisäätely aistiminen huone autismi suunnittelu Suomi" + "aistihuone Snoezelen kritiikki rajoitus näyttö autismi Suomi"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: PARTIAL ALIGNMENT. Finnish practice values user choice in aistihuone. Participatory design example (Autismisäätiö Kotka) is strong. But Käypä hoito positions low-stimulus environment as primary, aistihuone as supplement — same pattern as NL. Finnish evidence is practice-descriptive (theses), not experimental.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','EN','SEARCHED',4,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION

Scoping review (2024) found SAE evidence from 9 countries. User control confirmed as primary variable. Adversarial: SAEs ''not tailored to sensory needs of each child''; studies lack methodological rigor; implementation barriers (location, staffing).','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','ES','SEARCHED',4,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Sala multisensorial well-established in Spanish-speaking world. autismo.org.es (Confederación Autismo España): SHX interactive systems allow user to activate only desired stimuli. User control confirmed: "estimulación bajo control del usuario" (RecursosTEA). Chile: Ley de Autismo N°21.545 requires schools to adapt spaces for ASD — regulatory driver for sensory rooms. Qinera (SHX vendor, Spanish-language blog): requires "conocimiento profundo del perfil sensorial" before use; therapeutic intention essential. Epilepsy noted as contraindication (Fundacion Hospitalarias Ciempozuelos).
ADVERSARIAL: (1) RecursosTEA: "Los estudios sobre personas con autismo y salas multisensoriales son ESCASOS" (scarce); "todavía son limitadas" (still limited); more research needed to certify effectiveness. (2) Spanish OT thesis (UMH Elche): notes limited research on autism + SI model specifically. (3) Qinera blog challenges passive use: "No se trata simplemente de entrar en la sala para relajarse" — needs clear therapeutic intention, not just user free-choice. (4) No CTE DB SUA standard for sensory room design.
SEARCH QUERIES: "sala sensorial autismo diseño control usuario España norma" + "sala multisensorial autismo crítica limitación evidencia control usuario"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: PARTIAL ALIGNMENT. Spanish-language sources support user control as design value but acknowledge thin evidence base specifically for autism populations. Practice is closer to FR model (professional-guided with user responsiveness) than to BPC''s user-control-as-primary.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','ZH','SEARCHED',3,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Chinese framework is 感觉统合训练室 (SI training room) — practitioner-directed clinical intervention, NOT user-controlled sensory room. GB 50763 covers physical accessibility only, no sensory room provisions. Chinese rehabilitation centers often replicate kindergarten designs without autism-specific adaptations (Chu & Lee 2023, PeerJ CS). SR+MA (PMC12673401) systematically reviews SI effectiveness for Chinese autistic children — treats SI as clinical intervention.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) ALSOLIFE (major CN autism platform): SI training "一直存在争议" (has always been controversial); supplementary to ABA only, never replacement; not needed for children without SI dysfunction. (2) Chinese research on autism educational space design "still in its infancy" (Chu & Lee 2023). (3) No GB standard for sensory rooms. (4) No Chinese-language evidence found supporting user-control-as-primary design variable — concept appears absent from Chinese discourse. User control in Chinese context means therapist adjusts based on child response, not child controls environment.
SEARCH QUERIES: "感官室 自闭症 设计 用户控制 标准" + "安静室 感觉统合室 自闭症 建筑设计 中国标准" + "感觉统合训练 自闭症 批评 证据不足 争议 中国"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: GENUINE DIVERGENCE. Chinese practice does NOT align with BPC prior. User control is not the primary design variable in Chinese sensory room practice — practitioner control is. This is not a translation gap; it reflects a different therapeutic model (clinical SI training vs. Snoezelen-derived user-autonomy approach).','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','IT','SEARCHED',2,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION

Updated from prior BPC extraction. Lebanese 10-year study (548 children, PMC) found combined sensory room + conventional therapy effective. Italian clinical trial (NCT06184802) testing MSE for ASD ages 3-6. Snoezelen concept adopted in Italian care settings. No UNI standard for sensory room design.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','KO','SEARCHED',3,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Korean SI therapy (감각통합치료) is well-established clinical intervention, delivered by OTs in private clinics (사설기관), welfare centers (복지관), hospitals. 2022 Korean SR found 10 studies, all positive effects — BUT predominantly single-subject designs. Korean Integrative Treatment (herbal medicine + Floortime + SET) is home-based (PMC9846134). No dedicated sensory room design standards in Korea. 편의증진법 (Accessibility Act) covers physical mobility only.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) 2022 Korean SR calls for higher quality evidence: "근거의 질적 수준이 높은 연구가 필요" (higher quality evidence needed). (2) 2015 status survey: some therapists conduct SI without evaluation, lacking theoretical understanding. (3) Floortime Korea: standard SI therapy NOT effective for Asperger''s — recommends social development approaches instead. (4) Active neurodiversity movement (나무위키 discourse) challenging medical model of autism.
SEARCH QUERIES: "감각통합치료 자폐 감각실 사용자 통제 효과 연구 한국" + "감각통합치료 한계 비판 근거부족 자폐 한국"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: DIVERGENCE (same pattern as ZH). No Korean evidence supports user-control-as-primary for sensory room design. Korean practice is entirely clinical/therapist-directed. Concept of user-controlled sensory rooms appears absent from Korean built environment discourse.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','SV','SEARCHED',3,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Sinnesrum established in Swedish habilitation (Korallen, Lagunen, Balderskolan). OT scoping review (Diva-portal 2018): positive effects on participation for ADHD/autism — but cited studies predominantly from US/UK. TFH 3000+ MSEs across Scandinavia. Interactive SHX systems emphasize "känslan av kontroll." No Boverket standard.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) SPEDUCULT/Lund University 2020 survey: NO nationwide network, NO certified education for MSE/Snoezelen in Sweden. Knowledge acquired through informal "experience-sharing," not evidence-based training. 27 sites surveyed, primarily serving intellectual disability, not autism-specific. (2) Uppsatser 2014 thesis: "Much of the equipment used in Snoezelen environments is NOT interactive, and interactive equipment can be hard for the user to access" — directly challenges user-control claim. (3) Swedish OT thesis cites Lotan & Gold 2009 finding of no significant effect.
SEARCH QUERIES: "sinnesrum autism design Sverige Boverket standard" + "sinnesrum Snoezelen kritik begränsning evidens autism Sverige"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: WEAK ALIGNMENT. User control valued in principle ("känslan av kontroll") but in practice: equipment often not interactive, staff not certified, knowledge base informal. Swedish evidence base relies on international studies (US/UK), not Swedish-origin research on user control.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','NL','SEARCHED',4,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Netherlands = Snoezelen origin country (Verheul/Hulsegge, De Hartenberg, 1970s). SHX interactive systems: "zélf controle uitoefenen" (exercising control themselves). Major suppliers: Nenko (35+ yr), rdgKompagne. Passive vs interactive explicitly distinguished. SOVAK care org: residents can use snoezelruimte when stressed, with adjusted possibilities "aan waar de cliënt op dat moment graag wil" (to what client wants). Prikkelarm (low-stimulus) design is the baseline for autism housing, NOT sensory stimulation.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) WorldwideSnoezelen.nl cites 2008 Dutch research: "er niet op de juiste manier gesnoezeld wordt" — NOT being done correctly in practice. (2) NWO (Dutch Research Council) funded project for "doelgericht en effectief handelen" — implies current practice lacks targeting/effectiveness. (3) Wikipedia: research is "scarce, with variable study designs." (4) SOVAK: for autism residents, low-stimulus environment is the PRIMARY design strategy; sensory rooms are SUPPLEMENTARY for stress management. This inverts the BPC framing where sensory room user-control is primary. (5) No NEN standard for sensory room design.
SEARCH QUERIES: "sensorische kamer autisme ontwerp Nederland snoezelruimte" + "Snoezelen effectiviteit bewijs autisme kritiek Nederland onderzoek"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: NUANCED ALIGNMENT. Origin country values user control ("zélf controle") but Dutch practice for autism housing prioritizes LOW-STIMULUS environment as primary design, with sensory rooms as supplementary. Implementation quality issues acknowledged. Evidence base recognized as thin even in origin country.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','PT','SEARCHED',4,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Snoezelen established in both Portugal and Brazil. PT: ISNA certification available; CRIAP specialization program. Multiple institutions (Irmãs Hospitaleiras, Multipsis). BR: PL 3098/24 mandates school sensory rooms (3 types). APAE Bauru Snoezelen since 2009. Airport sensory rooms. Mostafa ASPECTSS Index used. Portuguese key framing: "não-diretiva" (non-directive), "liberdade de escolha" (freedom of choice), "auto-controle" (self-control). PT educational article: "Snoezelen não tem de ocorrer somente nas denominadas salas Snoezelen, pois trata-se de uma filosofia" — it''s a philosophy, not just a room.
ADVERSARIAL: (1) No PT/BR-specific adversarial study found. International adversarial evidence (McKee 2007, Lotan & Gold 2009) applies. (2) Wikipedia confirms: "Research on the benefits of Snoezelen treatment is scarce, with variable study designs." (3) No NBR/ABNT or Portuguese NP standard for sensory room design. (4) BR legislative mandate (PL 3098/24) requires professional supervision — implicit acknowledgment that unsupervised use may be harmful.
SEARCH QUERIES: "sala sensorial autismo design controle utilizador Portugal Brasil norma" + "sala sensorial Snoezelen crítica limitação evidência autismo Brasil Portugal"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: PARTIAL ALIGNMENT. Portuguese-language sources strongly support user autonomy as principle ("auto-controle," "liberdade de escolha") — closer to BPC prior than FR/ZH/KO. But evidence base acknowledged as scarce globally.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','NO','SEARCHED',2,'PROTOCOL: FULL

STANDARD: Sanserom established in Norwegian habilitation and municipalities. Autismeforeningen documents sanserom in public spaces (airports, museums). Kunnskapsbanken describes MSE for active/passive sensory use. Design emphasis: "trygghet og brukerens behov." No TEK17 standard.
ADVERSARIAL: [Shared with DA — VISS Skanderborg adversarial findings apply to Scandinavian context generally. McKee et al. 2007 and Lotan & Gold 2009 both cited in Scandinavian reviews. No Norway-specific adversarial source found.]
SEARCH QUERIES: "sanserom autisme design bruker kontroll Norge Danmark" + "sanserom Snoezelen kritikk begrensning evidens autisme Norge Danmark"
PRIOR CHALLENGE: PARTIAL ALIGNMENT. Norwegian practice follows Snoezelen methodology with user-needs emphasis, but adversarial evidence from Scandinavian reviews challenges effectiveness for autism specifically.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('sensory-room-user-control','JA','SEARCHED',5,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION

Very active research scene. Narita Airport CozyRoom (2005). JIS pictogram standard for calm-down spaces. Cross-national JP/US/FR biometric study (Kimura et al. 2025, AIJ). Portable ''Inclusive Quiet Room'' concept (2024, AIJ). Japan emphasizes portable/temporary solutions over permanent rooms. Key term: カームダウンスペース (calm-down space) more current than 感覚室.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T19:35:00Z','session_2026-05-10c-protocol-redo.md');
