INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('school-environment-autism','DE','SEARCHED',3,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

Austrian study on spatial aspects and school wellbeing for autistic students — clear place-activity mapping, colors/light/acoustics/surfaces all impact wellbeing. TU Wien "Making Space for Autism" project — participatory design WITH autistic students. TEACCH structured environments widely used but "empirisch ungenügend erforscht" (insufficiently researched empirically). No DIN standard specific to autism school design.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "Autismus Schule Raumgestaltung Kritik Einschränkung Evidenz"; "TEACCH Autismus Evidenz Kritik empirisch ungenügend"
FINDINGS:
- Swiss BA thesis (Zenodo 3691694): TEACCH "empirisch ungenügend erforscht" confirmed
- Swiss MA thesis (autismus.ch): RCTs ethically impossible; ABA only well-established intervention per US HHS 1999
- DE sources focus on PEDAGOGICAL accommodations (seating, visual structure, retreat spaces), NOT architectural specifications
- Bundesverband Autismus Deutschland: no "perfect school" — needs highly individual
- No DIN standard for autism school design
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: TEACCH structured environment (undergirding BPC spatial recs) has acknowledged evidence limitations. No DE evidence for NC-25 or NRC thresholds in autism school contexts.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:36:02Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('school-environment-autism','FR','SEARCHED',4,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

Negroni Architects ''L''Éveil du Scarabée'' (Auxerre 2014) — award-winning autism care building. Indirect lighting, LED only (no fluorescent), acoustic traps, visual escape lines. IME Boulogne-Billancourt purpose-built. Longuépée doctoral thesis (Univ Savoie) on architecture and ASD. NF EN ISO 10140-3/717-2 acoustic standards relevant. French ''architecture sensitive'' concept well-developed for autism institutional settings, less for mainstream schools.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "école autisme architecture critique limitation preuve inclusive"
FINDINGS:
- Abdelmoula et al. 2024 (European Psychiatry, PMC11860188, DOI:10.1192/j.eurpsy.2024.272): Review confirms Mostafa ASPECTSS as only "evidence-based" autism design framework. Acoustics is ONE of seven concepts (not dominant per Simpson 2025).
- Hunt & Goetz 1997 (via comprendrelautisme.com): "limited studies directly on procedures to facilitate inclusion"
- French "école inclusive" legally mandated (Loi 2005-102) but focuses on pedagogical adaptation, not built environment
- No French building code for autism school design
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: FR literature frames acoustics as one factor among seven (ASPECTSS), not as dominant. No FR evidence for specific thresholds.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:36:02Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('school-environment-autism','DA','SEARCHED',1,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

Danish BR18 does not address autism school design specifically. Sensory Design I/S works with Center for Autism Denmark. Autismeplatform emphasizes individual sensory assessment. No specific Danish research on school built environment and autism located.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "skole autisme design Danmark inklusion akustik evidens"
FINDINGS:
- Katrinebjergskolen Aarhus: Mixed autism/neurotypical classes with structure, visual schedules, noise level indicators — pedagogical, not architectural
- Landsforeningen Autisme (1,627 families): Poor wellbeing, stress, anxiety, school avoidance. "No evidence students benefit academically from special schools."
- Center for Autisme: Focus on structured pedagogy, not built environment
- Danish inclusion law 2012 — inclusion attempted but "many children not doing well"
- No BR18 standard for autism school design
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: Large-scale Danish survey confirms environmental challenges but frames as pedagogical/organizational, not architectural.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:36:02Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('school-environment-autism','FI','SEARCHED',1,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

Käypä hoito guidelines address sensory regulation for autism. Autismiliitto guidance on sensory-friendly spaces. Aistihuone in some schools. Finnish building code does not specifically address autism school design. Ecophon/Lahti reference on school acoustics generally relevant.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "koulu autismi suunnittelu kritiikki rajoitus näyttö inkluusio Suomi"
FINDINGS:
- Autismiliitto: CRITICAL — explicitly names "avoimet oppimisympäristöt" (open learning environments) as problematic: "noise, excessive visual stimuli, lack of structure, changing/large groups, unpredictable transitions burden autistic students." DIRECTLY supports noise+visual claim but as critique of modern Finnish open-classroom architecture.
- Käypä hoito: ABA evidence "largely insufficient and unreliable" with "unresolved ethical problems"
- Opetushallitus (2025 reform): Includes "modifying learning environments, e.g., arranging calming spaces or making noisy spaces less reverberant (vähemmän kaikuisiksi)" — CLOSEST any language comes to specific acoustic action
- Helsinki University: Inclusion became "a good enemy" — concept misunderstood
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: FI explicitly connects OPEN LEARNING ENVIRONMENTS (architectural trend) with negative outcomes. Opetushallitus mentions making spaces "less reverberant." No specific NC/NRC thresholds but strongest built-environment connection of any non-EN language.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:36:02Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');
