INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('school-environment-autism','PT','SEARCHED',2,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

Brazil PL 3098/24 mandating sensory rooms in schools. IFPB "sala de autorregulação" project uses Mostafa ASPECTSS Index. Brazilian academic work on autism rehabilitation space design exists but mainstream school design is nascent. No NBR standard.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "escola autismo projeto crítica limitação evidência inclusão Brasil"
FINDINGS:
- SciELO systematic review: Only 19 qualifying articles on autism inclusion in Brazilian schools — very thin evidence base
- PL 3098/24 (sensory rooms mandate) still under discussion, not law
- Gap between law (Lei 13.146/2015) and practice consistently noted
- Mostafa ASPECTSS referenced via IFPB sala de autorregulação
- No NBR/ABNT standard for autism school design
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: Extremely thin PT-language evidence base for any school-environment claim. No specific acoustic/visual thresholds.
