INSERT OR IGNORE INTO search_languages (slug,language,status,results_count,notes,created_at,created_by_session,updated_at,updated_by_session) VALUES ('school-environment-autism','JA','SEARCHED',1,'PROTOCOL: PRE-REMEDIATION (pre-DR-2026-05-09 baseline; bulk-marked Stage B.5)

TEACCH well-known in Japan (構造化). Japanese Autism Spectrum Society active. No specific JA research on school built environment for autism found — searched 自閉症 学校建築 教室設計 音響. Japan Autism Spectrum Society journal exists but no school architecture papers located.
ADVERSARIAL SEARCHED: "自閉症 学校環境 批判 限界 TEACCH 構造化 問題"
FINDINGS:
- Hasegawa 2024 (note.com): TEACCH philosophy not properly understood in Japan; 構造化 (structuring) extracted and applied in isolation, leading to criticism. Once seen as "magic method," now reduced to mere technique.
- Uchiyama (Ritsumeikan): Schools claiming TEACCH use identical picture cards/schedules for ALL students without understanding cognitive disability concept. Mechanical application without understanding WHY.
- No JA research on school BUILT environment for autism found. All sources focus on pedagogical/therapeutic environments.
ADVERSARIAL VALUE: JA confirms TEACCH structured environment criticized for mechanical application. No JA evidence for acoustic/visual specifications.
PROTOCOL COMPLIANCE: FULL — standard + adversarial searched, protocol fields populated.','2026-05-09 05:35','session_2026-05-09-search-coverage','2026-05-10T20:36:02Z','session_2026-05-10e-slug3-adversarial');

